      <p align="left"><strong><font color="#F13C29" size="1" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif">EDGE PERSPECTIVES</font></strong></p>
      <p><font color="#000000" size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><em>Insights   from Deloitte's <br>
        Center for the Edge</em></strong></font></p>
      <p><font color="#000000" size="2" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif"><strong><a href="http://dupress.com/articles/a-movement-in-the-making/">A Movement in the Making</a></strong><br>
The maker movement is an important manifestation of the economic landscape to come. Companies would be well served to find ways to participate, learn, and perhaps <em>shape</em> the movement. The maker movement brings disruptions but also opportunities: to boost sensing capabilities, leverage platforms for R&amp;D, accelerate learning, and reimagine the enterprise as a platform.</font></p>
